      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LIMOUSINE CHEEKY (1) led and faded last start at Penrith but had some decent form prior including a 3.5m third from a wide draw three back at Newcastle. Owns a good record at this circuit and distance so is better placed and has the speed to take advantage of the ace draw. KATASTROPHEE (5) drew on the back row and wasn't beaten far at her latest appearance at this circuit and distance, finishing 1.6 metres from the winner when fourth. Won from similar draw to this last month at Narrabri. Primary contender. EIFFEL FROM HEAVEN (6) has a strong record at this circuit and distance is significant. Won here two back then came from the back row when beaten only 5m last time out. Major player with even luck. TAFL MOVE (4) drops in grade off recent attempts and did a good job for second here two back.",
